    {
      "id": "rLMgPHffXu8IEglFQgsnV",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 249,
      "y": 1077,
      "width": 1290.3787841796875,
      "height": 350,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1610709684,
      "version": 1244,
      "versionNonce": 1907728652,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773832324320,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We can not use HTTP because each and every time client receives a message it can not keep sending HTTP request and server\ncan not send HTTP request to client.\nWe can use other techniques like -> Polling, long polling and Websockets.\n(i) Polling -> In polling clients does a TCP connection and asks is there a message, server will respond and connection closes.\nBut client has to keep asking and each time it needs to open connection. THis is not feasible.\n(ii) Long polling -> Client will ask is there a message, but server will not respond immediately. It will wait till a threshold and then\nreplies and closes the connection.\nBut this is also not feasible because server get held for that threshold time and it will not be scalable in huge application.\n(iii) Web socket -> It creates a bidirectional channel and it will be open till one of them closes or breaks the connection.\nSo messages are sent in same connection.\nSo we select web socket for chat system design.\n\nThere are 2 types of chat :\n(i) One to One : Here client and server are connected from ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 343,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We can not use HTTP because each and every time client receives a message it can not keep sending HTTP request and server\ncan not send HTTP request to client.\nWe can use other techniques like -> Polling, long polling and Websockets.\n(i) Polling -> In polling clients does a TCP connection and asks is there a message, server will respond and connection closes.\nBut client has to keep asking and each time it needs to open connection. THis is not feasible.\n(ii) Long polling -> Client will ask is there a message, but server will not respond immediately. It will wait till a threshold and then\nreplies and closes the connection.\nBut this is also not feasible because server get held for that threshold time and it will not be scalable in huge application.\n(iii) Web socket -> It creates a bidirectional channel and it will be open till one of them closes or breaks the connection.\nSo messages are sent in same connection.\nSo we select web socket for chat system design.\n\nThere are 2 types of chat :\n(i) One to One : Here client and server are connected from ",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
