      "versionNonce": 1165326260,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1773832651469,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "For storing the chat history ->\nUse NoSQL DB like Caasandra DB (its a column wise DB).\n\n\nIf connection to one server is down and User 2 is connected to it.\nNow user 1 wants to send message to user 2.\nIt sends message and user mapping service will check for server which is down.\nThen there is no entry to user 2, service will store this request in DB.\nNow user 2 restores internet and try to login and go to user mapping service,\nand it will find one chat server to user 2, for example chat server 3.\nIf there are some messages are pending then it would be sent to new chat server.\n\n\n(ii) Group message :\nIt will be similar but we will have a column for groupId also.\n ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 393,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "For storing the chat history ->\nUse NoSQL DB like Caasandra DB (its a column wise DB).\n\n\nIf connection to one server is down and User 2 is connected to it.\nNow user 1 wants to send message to user 2.\nIt sends message and user mapping service will check for server which is down.\nThen there is no entry to user 2, service will store this request in DB.\nNow user 2 restores internet and try to login and go to user mapping service,\nand it will find one chat server to user 2, for example chat server 3.\nIf there are some messages are pending then it would be sent to new chat server.\n\n\n(ii) Group message :\nIt will be similar but we will have a column for groupId also.\n ",
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
